    <note type="biography">
        <p>Manufacturing optician. Nephew of Joseph Jackson Lister (<hi rend="italic">DNB</hi>), whose design for achromatic objective lenses transformed microscope technology. Apprenticed to James Smith (Turner 1989), a mathematical instrument-maker in London. Entered into partnership as Smith &amp; Beck, 1847 – <hi rend="italic">c.</hi> 1857; as Smith, Beck &amp; Beck, <hi rend="italic">c.</hi> 1857–65; as R. &amp; J. Beck, 1865–6. Elected member of the Microscopical Society, 1855.</p></note>
